info.helpText:
Players sit in seats. Press the black and white restart button in the top center to randomly assign a starting player.  Click the roll dice button to start. Each player makes desired selections on their scoresheet by clicking the number to mark it.  Click the space again if a mistake was made to unmark it. When the current player finishes, the next player clicks the roll dice button. Play continues in that fashion.

If a player chooses not to make a mark when required to by rule, click on the white box at the end of the row. When a colored dice has been closed, click on the down arrow below the dice to hide it offscreen and block future changes to that color on the scoreboards. If a mistake is made, the dice can be returned to play by clicking on the up arrow.

Scoring is automatic for each player whenever the blue button with the sigma symbol is pressed. Typically you would wait until the end of the game to press it, but it can be used at any point in the game.
